Resident Evil - Code: Veronica [NTSC-U] *REPACK 2*
--------------------------------------------------
Ripped: Nothing.
Downsampled: Some videos, some audio (read notes).
Source: GD dump.

Good, here I am again with another repack, of course better than the last release.

The voices in 44khz were downsampled to 32khz (same frequency of almost all voices in the game).
and the audio of videos were also downsampled to 32khz (still stereo). With that, all audio of the
game are now at 32khz. Most of them was 32khz already, so you won't be able to notice any
difference.

I've used a better video encoder this time, so the videos got better and smaller. Additionally,
I had more space because of the audio. Only the opening video in first disc was downsampled, and
in second disc, about 60% of the videos. Note that when I say downsampled, I mean re-encoded.
Except for very dark scenes, the video quality difference between my videos and the original ones
won't be noticeable.

About performance, file order is more optimized than last time, and my last optimization techniques
were used.

Additionally, PAL 60hz patch for both discs are included in the pack. If you have a PAL console,
apply the patch before burning to make the game boot in 60hz. Note that it also fixes the de-sync
issues in animation that happens in 50hz. If you have a NTSC console, don't worry about that.

I hope it's the last time I work in this game. I'm proud of my clever choices in this release, and
I'm sure you'll like it either. Have fun.

