Resident Evil - Code: Veronica [NTSC-U] *REPACK*
------------------------------------------------
Ripped: Nothing.
Downsampled: Some videos.
Source: GD dump.

This game is great and I knew I could release it with much better quality than last time. Now
I downsampled videos myself, but I didn't have to downsample them all. In first disc, only
opening video is downsampled. In second, around half of videos are downsampled. I let audio of
videos untouched. Videos that were re-encoded, were made using VBR in the same bitrate as the
original video, so quality is very close to the original. Making a short explanation: videos are
great. Much better than my first release, and I'm sure that they're much better than the other
releases around.

I've used a custom file order based on GD original one, so you can expect great performance. This
is the best release possible of this great game, so grab it while you can.

Features of my release:
- Not corrupted files at all, it was made with GD dump files.
- Dummied for 700mb CDs.
- Used custom file order. It helps loading times and Dreamcast reader noise.
- Selfboot.

About the game:
- It has VGA Box support.

Other comments:
- "Extras" folder in the pack contains some useless stuff.
- Release comes with manual and covers.